ransform the city to create spaces of belonging and forms of citizenship anchored in a long history of resistance to extractive economies. Taking readers into the remnants of failed industrial projects in Haitian provinces and into the streets, rubble, and homes of Port-au-Prince, this book reflects on the possibilities and meanings of dwelling in post-disaster urban landscapes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEarthquake reliefzHaitixHistoryy21st century. 0aHaiti Earthquake, Haiti, 2010xEconomic aspects. 0aHaiti Earthquake, Haiti, 2010xSocial aspects. 0aHousingzHaiti. 0aInfrastructure (Economics)zHaiti. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aurban planning, Haiti, urban dwellings, neighborhoods, culture, earthquake, disaster relief, shelter, Port-au-Prince, UN, NGO, 2010 earthquake, Caribbean studies, housing, memory, daily life, post-disaster, urban studies, economic development, international aid, Northern Haiti, shotgun neighborhood, indigenous urbanization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076647940uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882062340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978820623423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978820623/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-076647-9  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  a